    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="495"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Buck</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 257.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch, No. 350, of the 7th ultimo, confirming your telegram of the 2d ultimo,
                    reporting the beaching of the United States transport <hi rend="italic">Morgan
                        City</hi>, and giving further information on the subject.</p>
                <p>You will express this Government’s appreciation of the courteous aid tendered to
                    the vessel and her crew and passengers in the several quarters mentioned in your
                    dispatch.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
